{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "easyvtc-vehicle-types-crud",
    "name": "EasyVTC — Types de véhicule (CRUD)",
    "description": "# EasyVTC — Module vehicle-types\n\n## Setup\n1. Importer cette collection **et** l'environnement `EasyVTC_Local`\n2. Vérifier que `admin_email` / `admin_password` sont renseignés dans l'environnement\n3. Lancer l'API : `npm run dev`\n4. Appliquer la migration : `20260422000001_vehicle_types_table.sql` (seed les 3 types standard/berline/van)\n5. Exécuter **🔐 Authentification** en premier, puis suivre l'ordre numéroté\n\n## Routes couvertes\n```\nGET    /vehicle-types                     (public)\nGET    /admin/vehicle-types               (admin)\nGET    /admin/vehicle-types/:id           (admin)\nPOST   /admin/vehicle-types              (admin)\nPATCH  /admin/vehicle-types/:id          (admin)\nDELETE /admin/vehicle-types/:id          (admin)\n```\n\n## Variables sauvegardées automatiquement\n- `admin_token` — après le login admin\n- `vehicle_type_id` — après `POST /admin/vehicle-types` (type de test `minibus-test`)",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "base_url",         "value": "http://localhost:4000", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "admin_token",      "value": "",                      "type": "string" },
    { "key": "vehicle_type_id",  "value": "",                      "type": "string", "description": "UUID du type créé par POST (minibus-test) — sauvegardé automatiquement" }
  ],
  "item": [

    {
      "name": "🔐 Authentification",
      "description": "Exécuter en premier pour peupler admin_token.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Login Admin",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/login", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["auth", "login"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{admin_email}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{admin_password}}\"\n}"
            }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "pm.test('admin_token sauvegardé', () => {",
            "  const json = pm.response.json();",
            "  pm.expect(json.ok).to.be.true;",
            "  pm.expect(json.data.user.role).to.equal('admin');",
            "  pm.collectionVariables.set('admin_token', json.data.access_token);",
            "  console.log('✅ admin_token sauvegardé');",
            "});"
          ]}}]
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "name": "1️⃣ GET /vehicle-types — Endpoint public",
      "description": "Endpoint public (sans authentification). Retourne uniquement les types actifs avec un base_price unique selon le pays.",
      "item": [

        {
          "name": "GET /vehicle-types — sans filtre (France par défaut)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/vehicle-types",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["vehicle-types"]
            }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "const json = pm.response.json();",
            "const data = json.data;",
            "",
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "pm.test('ok: true', () => pm.expect(json.ok).to.be.true);",
            "pm.test('data est un tableau', () => pm.expect(data).to.be.an('array'));",
            "pm.test('Au moins 3 types actifs (seed)', () => pm.expect(data.length).to.be.at.least(3));",
            "",
            "pm.test('Structure VehicleTypePublic valide', () => {",
            "  data.forEach(t => {",
            "    pm.expect(t, `type ${t.code}`).to.have.all.keys('code', 'label', 'description', 'capacity', 'icon', 'base_price');",
            "  });",
            "});",
            "",
            "pm.test('Les 3 types du seed sont présents', () => {",
            "  const codes = data.map(t => t.code);",
            "  pm.expect(codes).to.include('standard');",
            "  pm.expect(codes).to.include('berline');",
            "  pm.expect(codes).to.include('van');",
            "});",
            "",
            "pm.test('base_price est un nombre positif (France)', () => {",
            "  data.forEach(t => {",
            "    pm.expect(t.base_price, `base_price de ${t.code}`).to.be.a('number').and.greaterThan(0);",
            "  });",
            "});",
            "",
            "pm.test('standard : 12.50 € (France)', () => {",
            "  const standard = data.find(t => t.code === 'standard');",
            "  if (standard) pm.expect(standard.base_price).to.equal(12.5);",
            "});",
            "",
            "pm.test('Pas de champs admin (pas de is_active, base_price_france, etc.)', () => {",
            "  data.forEach(t => {",
            "    pm.expect(t).to.not.have.property('is_active');",
            "    pm.expect(t).to.not.have.property('base_price_france');",
            "    pm.expect(t).to.not.have.property('base_price_senegal');",
            "  });",
            "});"
          ]}}]
        },

        {
          "name": "GET /vehicle-types?country=france — prix France",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/vehicle-types?country=france",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["vehicle-types"],
              "query": [{ "key": "country", "value": "france" }]
            }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "const data = pm.response.json().data;",
            "",
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "",
            "pm.test('standard : 12.50 € (France)', () => {",
            "  const s = data.find(t => t.code === 'standard');",
            "  if (s) pm.expect(s.base_price).to.equal(12.5);",
            "});",
            "",
            "pm.test('berline : 18.00 € (France)', () => {",
            "  const b = data.find(t => t.code === 'berline');",
            "  if (b) pm.expect(b.base_price).to.equal(18);",
            "});",
            "",
            "pm.test('van : 35.00 € (France)', () => {",
            "  const v = data.find(t => t.code === 'van');",
            "  if (v) pm.expect(v.base_price).to.equal(35);",
            "});"
          ]}}]
        },

        {
          "name": "GET /vehicle-types?country=senegal — prix Sénégal (XOF)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/vehicle-types?country=senegal",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["vehicle-types"],
              "query": [{ "key": "country", "value": "senegal" }]
            }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "const data = pm.response.json().data;",
            "",
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "",
            "pm.test('standard : 3000 XOF (Sénégal)', () => {",
            "  const s = data.find(t => t.code === 'standard');",
            "  if (s) pm.expect(s.base_price).to.equal(3000);",
            "});",
            "",
            "pm.test('berline : 5000 XOF (Sénégal)', () => {",
            "  const b = data.find(t => t.code === 'berline');",
            "  if (b) pm.expect(b.base_price).to.equal(5000);",
            "});",
            "",
            "pm.test('van : 9000 XOF (Sénégal)', () => {",
            "  const v = data.find(t => t.code === 'van');",
            "  if (v) pm.expect(v.base_price).to.equal(9000);",
            "});"
          ]}}]
        },

        {
          "name": "GET /vehicle-types — résultats triés par sort_order",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/vehicle-types",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["vehicle-types"]
            }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "const data = pm.response.json().data;",
            "",
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "",
            "pm.test('Ordre : standard → berline → van (sort_order 1,2,3)', () => {",
            "  const codes = data.filter(t => ['standard','berline','van'].includes(t.code)).map(t => t.code);",
            "  const standardIdx = codes.indexOf('standard');",
            "  const berlineIdx  = codes.indexOf('berline');",
            "  const vanIdx      = codes.indexOf('van');",
            "  if (standardIdx !== -1 && berlineIdx !== -1) pm.expect(standardIdx).to.be.lessThan(berlineIdx);",
            "  if (berlineIdx !== -1 && vanIdx !== -1) pm.expect(berlineIdx).to.be.lessThan(vanIdx);",
            "});"
          ]}}]
        }

      ]
    },

